		"description": "<p dir=\"ltr\">With a hand going to your upper chest and a brief rebuke you cause your target consternation, and force them to reword themself.</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">As a reaction to your target making a successful social maneuver you create the brief illusion that they have said something scandalous, scurrilous, or otherwise unfit for polite or mixed company. On a failed saving throw the target&rsquo;s successful skill or ability check is instead treated as a failure.</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">A creature that witnesses you using this spell can roll an insight check against your passive Deception to recognize that a spell has been cast.</p>",
